<HEADLINE>
GUNMAN WOUNDS 4 IN HOUSTON-AREA CHURCH, KILLS SELF 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds.: trim indicator included) 
 
By JERRY URBAN 
and RUTH RENDON 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ A man angry over being spurned by a woman walked into
a Houston-area church Wednesday night and shot four people before
killing himself.
</P>
<P>
   Two of the wounded were listed in critical condition late
Wednesday, a third was in fair condition and the fourth suffered
only a minor wound.
</P>
<P>
   Pasadena police Sgt. Mike Baird said the man, angry with a woman
who had refused to be his girlfriend, walked into Iglesia Esposa
del Cordero Pentecostal Church about 9 p.m. with a semiautomatic
pistol.
</P>
<P>
   Baird said he shot the woman, 18-year-old Leslie Contreras, her
38-year-old mother, Angela Contreras, the 49-year-old church
pastor, Carlos Matamores, and an unidentified 32-year-old man.
</P>
<P>
   The man, still unidentified late Wednesday, then went into the
church parking lot in suburban Pasasdena and fatally shot himself.
</P>
<P>
   Pasadena, a pretrochemical area with about 134,000 residents, is
about 10 miles southeast of downtown Houston.
</P>
<P>
   The mother and pastor were flown to Memorial Hermann Hospital in
Houston with life-threatening wounds, hers in the abdomen, his in
the chest.
</P>
<P>
   Leslie Contreras was taken by ambulance to Ben Taub Hospital in
Houston with a neck wound, hospital officials said. An official
said the injury is not life threatening, but that she would be kept
overnight.
</P>
<P>
   The 32-year-old man was ``grazed across the chest,'' Baird said,
and did not have to be taken to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Baird said the gunman ``apparently was in love with the
18-year-old female (and) ... she told him she liked him like a
brother, but just didn't want to be his girlfriend.''
</P>
<P>
   Baird said the man then told her ``something bad was fixing to
happen,'' walked out of the church, which was ``full of folks,''
then returned to shoot the four people.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(BEGIN OPTIONAL TRIM) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Church member Jose Montana, 34, said he saw the man Wednesday
morning at a nearby Wal-Mart. He said he was making small talk with
the man _ whom he knew only as ``Oscar'' _ when ``he said he was
going to kill someone.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought he was kidding,'' Montana said. ``I told myself that
if I saw him at the church tonight I would call police.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(END OPTIONAL TRIM) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It was the second church shooting in Texas in the last six
months.
</P>
<P>
   A gunman killed seven people and wounded seven others before
killing himself Sept. 15 during a youth rally at Wedgwood Baptist
Church in Fort Worth.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY XXXXX &QL; 
