<P>
   MOBY _ Whatever you do, don't call him a DJ. That's the first
lesson learned in a brief telephone conversation with Moby (real
name Richard Melville Hall), the electronic artist who has gone
from acareer on the club circuit to mainstream success, replete
with regular radio play, a couple of Grammy nominations and a spot
on the current ``MTV Campus Invasion'' tour that hits FAU Friday.
It's not that Moby, whose moniker derives from the fact he's a
direct descendent of ``Moby Dick'' author Herman Melville, can't
spin records with the best of them. It's that he chooses to define
his artistic life in broader terms. By
</P>
<P>
   (Passy, Palm Beach Post). 22.
</P>
<P>
   BAND-REVIEW _ Review of new ABC show, Making the Band, three
stars. It's an intriguing behind-the-scenes look at the making of a
pop music band. By KEVIN (Thompson, Palm Beach Post).
