   BOOKS-ODONOHUE _ John O'Donohue found himself in California on
St. Patrick's Day this year, where he did not drink green beer or
wear a shamrock. Americans, it seems, have gotten a bit carried
away. It was almost enough to send him running back to his native
County Clare, Ireland. But he stuck around for his national book
tour, which brings him to Books &AMP; Co. in Kettering to promote his
latest spiritual effort, Eternal Echoes: Celtic Reflections on Our
Yearning to Belong (Cliff Street Books, $25). (Dayton Daily News).
