<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-TB-DAY _ Friday is World TB Day. Though the
lung-destroying illness often is thought of as something that
belongs to Victorian novels _ or to the Third World _ it's a
problem in the United States as well: Georgia is among the 10 worst
states for TB, according to national figures, and the number of
cases is rising. Also rising is the number of cases among
foreign-born migrants to Georgia, from Latino landscapers and
food-service personnel in Cobb County to graduate students at
Georgia Tech. In Georgia, it is even more costly than it needs to
be, advocates and health experts say, because the state has not
applied to Medicaid for reimbursement for TB treatment, meaning
that it misses out on several million dollars each year that the
other TB-heavy states receive. (McKenna, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION
</P>
<P>
   So specialty editors can focus on one day's budget, CoxNet
produces themed features budgets each day. Here is the schedule:
</P>
<P>
   Monday for Tuesday: Technology
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday for Wednesday: Automotive, personal finance and home &AMP;
garden
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday for Thursday: Food, CD reviews, video reviews
</P>
<P>
   TODAY: Movie reviews, travel, books and fashion
</P>
<P>
   Friday for Saturday: Religion and science &AMP; health
</P>
<P>
   In addition, separate budgets move daily with spot news, sports,
business and commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the category they're listed under. Stories
moving to duplicate categories are marked. An ETA is given if a
story will move after 8 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
