<P>
   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-DRAWL (Houston) _ What does your accent say about you? In
the presidential race, George Dubbya drops g's from the end of
every word _ he's wish`, hopin` and thinkin` _ and sounds Texas
folksy. It seems to work for politicians and socialites but not
always in the business world or on TV either. A look at the prose
and cons of having a Texas accent, or any accent for that matter.
By CLIFFORD PUGH.
</P>
<P>
   BARBER-FAMILY (Houston) _ Whenever the Ortuno family gets
together, you could say it's a hair-raising experience. Ezequiel
Ortuno is a barber. So is his brother, Amado. And his other
brother, Manuel. Sister Janete Ortuno Castro is also a barber. All
told, there are some 60 Ortuno-family cousins who live in Houston;
almost all are barbers. Some have wives who are barbers. Get
anywhere near the Ortuno family, it seems, and you get the urge to
cut hair. By MELISSA FLETCHER STOELTJE (Photo available on NYT
database)
</P>
<P>
   WAVING-MAN (Berkeley, Calif.) _ Joseph Charles has waved his way
onto the national news, into the hearts of thousands and into his
10th decade. Some 50 admirers gathered at a restaurant Wednesday
night to celebrate the 90th birthday of Berkeley's famous Waving
Man. It's been eight years since Charles retired from his
celebrated hobby of waving to passing cars at the corner of Oregon
Street and Martin Luther King Way, a hobby he enjoyed for 30 years.
By MICHAEL DOUGAN.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GARAGE-DOOR-TRIAL (San Francisco) _ As the fire overwhelmed her,
Melanie Stapper says she clawed at the garage door. She passed out
with her head on the floor, trying in vain to inhale oxygen from
outside. The 39-year-old former firefighter lived through the March
1995 blaze to hire lawyers and sue Genie, claiming a malfunctioning
door opener trapped her in the garage. By PETER HARTLAUB.
</P>
<P>
   EMERGENCY-CARE (San Francisco) _ Californians needing emergency
care have become the latest victims of the state's health care
crisis, as the number of emergency rooms shrinks, overcrowding
becomes chronic and specialists are refusing to be ``on call'' for
complex cases.
</P>
<P>
   By ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-TOMMY-LEE (Undated) _ Musician Tommy Lee, who was once
married to Heather Locklear and Pamela Anderson, is touring with
rapper Tilo and performing as Methods of Mayhem. By MICHAEL D.
CLARK.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-THERON (New York) _ Charlize Theron, who stars in the
action-thriller ``Reindeer Games'' and Oscar-nominated ``The Cider
House Rules,'' talks about leaving her It Girl status behind to
become a respected actress. By LOUIS B. PARKS.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-REVIEW (Undated) _ Reviews of films ``Pokemon: The First
Movie'' and a special edition DVD of ``The Abyss.'' By BRUCE
WESTBROOK.
</P>
<P>
   TV-DADDIO (Undated) _ Why NBC doesn't throw in the towel is
beyond understanding. The network has only a few quality shows left
and its new shows this season outside of ``West Wing'' have been
embarrassingly bad. What it really ought to do is join ABC in
giving up entirely _ just use Regis Philbin to mop up and turn out
the lights. Forget sitcoms and dramas. Go with a game show. By TIM
GOODMAN.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD (``d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CARROTT-CAKE (Undated) _ There are two ways to make carrot cake:
Spend a day in the kitchen grating carrots and beating eggs, or use
a mix. But with most mixes, you get some wimpy cake that tastes
more like cinnamon than carrots and has the texture of a Twinkie.
There is a middle ground. By RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
<P>
   PEPINO-FRUIT (Undated) _ When you saw them in the store, betcha
didn't know what they were. Pepino melons are one of those odd
things placed on the exotic fruit table. Like more common melons,
pepinos can be eaten raw but they are certainly now as big as a
crenshaw or a cantaloupe. They are also called melon pears because
of their demure size _ each one is only about the size of a hand _
and slightly elongated shape. By RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
</TEXT>
