<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-ARGYLE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     HEARST-ARGYLE TV JOINS CFN IN ALLIANCE 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     c.2000 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Hearst-Argyle Television, Inc. said Thursday that it
has formed a strategic alliance with Consumer Financial Network
(CFN), an online provider of consumer financial information and
services. As part of the alliance, Hearst-Argyle has made a $25
million equity investment in CFN, which will become a content
provider to and advertiser on Hearst-Argyle's television stations
and local websites.
</P>
<P>
   ``CFN is highly synergistic with our Internet strategy of being
a leading Web provider of consumer news, information and e-commerce
in our 24 local markets,'' said Bob Marbut, Hearst-Argyle chairman
and co-chief executive officer. ``Through our television stations
and our many local websites, developed with Internet Broadcasting
Systems (IBS), CFN gives us rich, personalized content and
e-commerce in the financial-services and health fields which are of
ever-greater importance to our customers.''
</P>
<P>
   Hearst-Argyle is CFN's first media partner. Other newly
announced investors include Capital Research and Management
Company, Chase Capital Partners LLC, Royal Bank of Canada, First
Union Corporation, J. &AMP; W. Seligman &AMP; Co., Equifax Communications,
Westway Capital LLC, and several private investors. This most
recent round of equity financing for CFN, totaling $130.5 million,
represents one of the largest rounds of equity funding for an
Internet company. GE Capital is one of CFN's original investors.
</P>
<P>
   CFN, headquartered in Atlanta, is building the premiere portal
for consumer financial and health needs at work and at home. For
corporations, CFN offers a suite of products that give companies
the most flexible and rapidly deployable manager and employee
self-service solution for benefits and human relations policies.
Today, this end-to-endsolution is anchored by iExpert, the premiere
knowledge management product on the market.
</P>
<P>
   CFN also operates YouDecide.com, an e-commerce web site for
marketing financial services and related benefits to individual
consumers over the Internet, to employees at corporations and
through retail partners such as Women.com and SmartMoney.com, which
are co-owned by The Hearst Corporation, Hearst-Argyle's majority
shareholder.
</P>
<P>
   CFN is a subsidiary of iXL Enterprises, Inc. Hearst-Argyle
Television, Inc. owns or manages 26 television stations and seven
radio stations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
