government scientists that the world's oceans have soaked up much
of the warming of the last half century, in effect delaying its
full effect on climate. By William K. Stevens.
</P>
<P>
   WALLST-BIAS (New York) _ Ending a two year probe into charges of
racism and sexual harassment that some employees say are
commonplace on Wall Street, the New York state attorney general
announced a settlement with two brokerage firms.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NY-THEATER-MURAL (New York) _ A long-forgotten actor, the toast
of 1900s Broadway and a star of silent films, will soon retake his
rightful place in the Times Square theater that bore his name for
decades. And, fittingly, he'll be doing it in drag. Julian Eltinge,
a once-famous female impersonator is thought to be depicted on a
mural that was lost for 60 years under layers of paint and that
will be unveiled later this month. By John Holusha.
