<P>
   (600 words) &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POPE ARRIVES IN THE LAND OF CHRIST _ AND CONTROVERSY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POPE-HOLYLAND-400&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ Pope John Paul II touched down in Jordan Monday to
begin the most ambitious and diplomatically perilous journey of his
22-year papacy, and at once made clear that he would not shy away
from the combustible issues of Middle East politics. Although on a
personal (and long dreamed of) spiritual mission to the land of
Christ and Moses, the pope also does not intend to be blind to the
issues that have so hopelessly divided the region...By Phil Reeves,
The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (NOTE: 100-word optional trim at 400; 925 words uncut) &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (RESENDING from March 14) &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BANGALORE OR HYDERABAD: TWO HIGH-TECH CITIES VIE FOR CLINTON
VISIT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CYBER-INDIA-CLINTON-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DELHI _ Which is it to be, Mr. Clinton? The American president
comes to India on March 20, the first such visit for 22 years, and
the subcontinent's two most strenuously forward-looking cities,
Bangalore and Hyderabad, are competing furiously for his attention.
Both are vying to become the most important center of India's
booming software industry but he will only visit one of them. Which
will it be?...By Peter Popham, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for Clinton's March 20 visit to India!) &QL;
</P>
