<P>
   NY-GIULIANI (New York) _ It's too early to say whether New
York's latest shooting by police will affect the Senate election.
But polls show the two candidates so close, and the number of
undecided voters so small, that even a slight shift will have
decisive consequences. By Fred Kaplan.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JACOBY-COLUMN (Undated) _ In politics, money isn't the root of
all evil. By Jeff Jacoby.
</P>
<P>
