<P>
   CARWASH-SLAYINGS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Mi-T-Fine Car Wash employee Jason Shields
stopped for doughnuts Monday morning and noticed three of his
co-workers ambling across a parking lot on their way to work.
Minutes later, Shields pushed open the front door of the carwash to
absorb a chilling scene: the same three co-workers sprawled in
puddles of blood, and a fired employee, Robert Wayne Harris,
blurting an equally terrifying remark. ``There's three more back
here in the office,'' Harris said, according to police affidavits.
Accompanied by CARWASH-SLAYINGS. By MILES MOFFEIT and MITCH
MITCHELL. Story will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CARWASH-DISAPPEARANCE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Already accused of killing five co-workers,
Robert Wayne Harris had something else he needed to tell police:
where to find a body. Wednesday morning, acting on Harris'
information, police found a body believed to be that of an Irving
woman missing since November. Accompanies CARWASH-SLAYINGS. By
GORDON DICKSON and SUSAN GILL VARDON. Story will move in ``a''
general news category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
