</P>
<P>
   BBN-GRIFFEY-IMPACT _ What does having Griffey really mean to the
Reds on the field? Cincinnati Reds fans are excited about the
coming season the way an 8-year-old kid is excited a couple of days
before Christmas. The Reds have baseball's best position player.
And they got him for a song. Their lineup is intact. Optimism
hasn't run this high since the Big Red Machine days. But in
reality, what impact will Junior Griffey have on this team, which
looks strong on offense, strong up the middle, weak at the corners.
And, oh, then there's the part of the game called pitching, a huge
question mark. (McCoy, Dayton Daily News). 25. WITH PHOTOS. WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBN-GRIFFEY-TRADE _ How might this trade compare to the one that
brought Joe Morgan, Jack Billingham and Caesar Geronimo to the
Reds, solidifying the Big Red Machine. (McCoy, Dayton Daily News).
15-18. MCKEON-GRIFFEY-MCKEON _ Now that Trader Jack has had Junior
Griffey on his team for a month, what's his take on this player?
What's their relationship? And what's Griffey's take on Ol' Trader?
Also, what's this heir apparent stuff with Griffey Sr.? (McCoy,
Dayton Daily News). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-REDS-LINEUP _ This is one of the most potent lineups in
baseball. It has Larkin, Casey, Griffey and Bichette back to back
to back to back. And jack
</P>
<P>
   rabbit Pokey Reese in front of them. What will opposing pitchers
do? Fans should love the run production. (McCoy, Dayton Daily
News). 15-18.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-REDS-BOWDEN _ Reds General Manager Jim Bowden is one of the
brightest in baseball. And the story has been told before, right?
Wrong. We want to know
</P>
<P>
   exactly why fate smiles on him so often and if he's in
Cincinnati to stay. (McCoy or McClelland, Dayton Daily News). 15.
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
