<HEADER>
A6062 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l BC-IDEAL-FACE24-COX     03-23 0486
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IDEAL-FACE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Our idea of beauty relies on structure, balance, skin
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The patrician looks of Elizabeth Hurley.
The brooding handsomeness of George Clooney. The exotic allure of
Halle Berry and the formal countenance of Pierce Brosnan.
</P>
<P>
   These famous folks' features won nods from the American Academy
of Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery as ``the ideal faces
of beauty'' in a recent survey of its members.
</P>
<P>
   Here are academy President Davinder Mangat's comments on who the
academy chose as fairest of them all.
</P>
<P>
   PIERCE BROSNAN
</P>
<P>
   ``He is not anything like George Clooney. George Clooney has a
masculine face that is well-proportioned. Pierce Brosnan has a
gentler, perfect face. He doesn't have masculine features in terms
of having that real strong nose, but he has softer features that
are still male features. He's got that `pretty boy' look.''
</P>
<P>
   GEORGE CLOONEY
</P>
<P>
   ``Most women think he's a hunk. That's because he has about as
masculine a face as you can find, but it's perfectly proportioned.
A strong nose. Big eyes. Good, strong eyebrows. And that's what
makes him attractive. On top of that, his personality comes through
in interviews and on screen.''
</P>
<P>
   BRAD PITT
</P>
<P>
   ``Overall, when you look at Brad Pitt and Pierce Brosnan, they
have very similar features. But the big difference is that smile.
When Brad Pitt smiles, it's more than his lips. His eyes smile with
him. And Brad Pitt has the bluest eyes out there.''
</P>
<P>
   SHARON STONE
</P>
<P>
   ``The ultimate feminine face of gentleness, the classic beauty.
She has the best skin you've ever seen that's covering bone
structures that couldn't be any more perfect. And she has the most
expressive eyes.'' Scientifically the most perfect of the group?
``I would say so.''
</P>
<P>
   HALLE BERRY
</P>
<P>
   ``She's beautiful because she has that skin that everybody
strives to achieve, which looks naturally tanned. But the biggest
thing is that she has facial features that are so commonly present
in individuals that are biracial. It's a mixture of races that so
often brings out very unique features, features that are not
commonplace.''
</P>
<P>
   GWYNETH PALTROW
</P>
<P>
   ``If she didn't have the personality and the smile and the
charisma that she has in the movies, Gwyneth Paltrow might be an
ordinary beauty. But she has so much life behind that face. And
remember that people acquire their opinions about a beautiful face
based not just on how a person looks, but what they know about
them.''
</P>
<P>
   ELIZABETH HURLEY
</P>
<P>
   A case of everything working in harmony. ``She's got an
interesting face, but at the same time she has very soft features.
She doesn't have any part of her face that's overwhelming. It's
just well-balanced. It projects very well.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
