<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    All quiet in the kitchen! Here's how to direct a winning Oscar
party
 &HT;    By Jan Norris
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _
</P>
<P>
   American Beauty Rose Petal Sorbet: In ``American Beauty,''
nominated for eight awards, Kevin Spacey fantasizes about his teen
daughter's seductive friend in a visually stunning naked pose on a
bed of rose petals. We're dreaming about this luscious rose petal
sorbet. It's simple and best of all, can be made days ahead.
(Remember to use pesticide-free flowers.) Tumbleweeds Chili Melt:
This updated version of the patty melt is our nod to road food, to
go along with ``Tumbleweeds.'' In this '90s road picture, Janet
McTeer was nominated for her portrayal of an immature mother in the
story of a mother-daughter romp across the United States. Kimberly
J. Brown plays the astute teen. For just a small party, these
sandwiches, tipped toward spicy with chili powder and jalapeno
cheese, are easy to make on a sandwich grill.
</P>
<P>
   Cider House Rules Apple Salad: Nominated for seven awards, this
movie features Michael Caine as head of a Maine orphanage. Scenes
of apple-picking inspired our crisp apple-potato salad nestled on a
bed of greens. The crumbled goat cheese and red-currant jelly
vinaigrette offer unusual taste contrasts as well. Have ingredients
ready for assembling this dish just before serving, to keep it
technicolor pretty.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
