</P>
<P>
   AMIN-QUESTIONS _ If Al-Amin wasn't shot, whose blood was it that
cops followed to an abandoned house? Was someone else with him?
What about the two kinds of shell casings (other than the police
issue)found at the scene? How did Al-Amin get out of town? And
where are those two cars? There are lots of unanswered questions.
We'll try to answer as many as we can? (Longa, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-CHAPLAIN _ The Rev. Charles Wright of Atlanta, whose
selection as House chaplain has kicked off a controversy about
alleged anti-Catholic bias among Republicans, says he has offered
to withdraw. (Carr, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CENSUS-RELIGION _ ATLANTA _ The federal government and houses of
worship plan to join hands to pray this weekend, crossing the great
constitutional divide that separates church and state in the spirit
of getting an accurate census count. The U.S. Bureau of the Census
has asked preachers, priests and rabbis, imams, lamas and gurus to
pitch the 2000 census in their sermons. (Cook, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
