scripture verses and sermon ideas to promote participation in the
census. Here are two samples. (Cook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
12.
</P>
<P>
   TENN-DEATHSTAY _ NASHVILLE _ Robert Glen Coe seemed likely to
become the first person to be executed in Tennessee in 40 years,
but a federal judge issued a brief stay of execution Wednesday,
indefinitely delaying his death. Unlike a lot of Southern cities
numbed by regular executions, Nashville practically was in mourning
Wednesday night with prayer vigils at many local churches. (Dubose,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancer; not for use by NYTNS
clients).
</P>
