<P>
   COKE-DIVERSE _ Coca-Cola promoted an African-American, Juan
Johnson, 42, from within the company to fill a newly created
position of diversity director. The move comes a day after the
company named a black executive to head human resources.(Unfer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   USAIRWAYS-IMPACT _ A possible shutdown at US Airways this
weekend could mean a scarcity of seats on Delta and AirTran as
passengers flock to other carriers. Checking with them to see if
bookings already are up because of the threat. Will wrap in update
on flight attendant talks. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   GAPAC-WEB _ Georgia-Pacific is teaming up with rivals
International Paper and Weyerhauser to create an
business-to-business Internet company for the buying and selling of
products online. Each company has an equal stake for now, but more
partners are expected to join. The companies are searching for a
CEO and a board of directors. If successful, the entity could go
public. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).10.
</P>
<P>
   CFN _ IXL Enterprises' Consumer Financial Network said it
received a $130.5 million private equity investment. Private equity
is money invested in more established private companies, those that
are a stage beyond beture capital. (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-HIGHTECH _ JAIPUR, India _ President Clinton will visit
the country's computer centers on Friday to bring attention to
India's growing siginificance as a world high technology center and
stress its growing importance to the U.S. computer industry.
Developing. (Deans, Cx News Service). 20.
