<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-CLINTON _ NAYLA, India _ Worried about the ``potential
failure'' of Pakistan and the dangers that could pose to South
Asia, President Clinton will lay out some ``hard realities'' when
he meets with the country's military
</P>
<P>
   government on Saturday, a senior White House official said
Thursday. Clinton will express U.S. support for Pakistan, a key
American ally during the Cold War. He'll also urge the country's
junta leaders to end support for paramilitary
</P>
<P>
