<P>
   CAR-RONNIESANDERS _ A year ago, Ronnie Sanders was a lot like
other drivers in the twilight of their careers. The victories,
which once came so easily, were eluding him and most of the
questions were about his retirement. But Sanders won the season
opener for the Southern All Stars in 1999 and went onto have one of
the best seasons of his career. Now, at age 54, he once again took
the season opener and comes to Saturday night's race at Peach State
Speedway in Jefferson, Ga., with the points lead. Sanders, who
drove some in Winston Cup but was never able to land a top ride, is
admired by his fellow racers for his hard work off the track and
his tenacity on it. (Minter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
