<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAVES-FIRSTPERSON24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `I can be myself _ whatever incarnation that may be'
 &HT;    By T. Chante LaGon
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It was the morning after a rave. My ears hadn't stopped ringing.
The smell of wet smoke lingered, and traces of purple eye shadow
and red mascara held on where sweat had erased everything else.
</P>
<P>
   Even now, I felt connected. Drained _ I smiled at the thought of
dancing so hard _ yet somehow energized by a force stronger than
the brilliant lasers that flashed across the dance floor.
</P>
<P>
   A rave is unforgettable. A good one changes your life.
</P>
<P>
   You start displaying PLUR _ peace, love, unity and respect _
every day. You are more open-minded. Giving strangers compliments
no longer seems strange.
</P>
<P>
   I believe that it takes a special person to be a raver. It takes
endurance. It takes a love for music that you won't hear on 99X or
Hot 97.5. Most of all, it requires a special mind-set.
</P>
<P>
   Ravers know there's something more than rush-hour traffic,
weekends in Buckhead or Sunday dinners: There's spirituality,
individuality, better living through music.
</P>
<P>
   When I walk into a party, the drums and bass remind me of my
hip-hop background. Eye candy is everywhere, from fairies and
``candy'' kids bejeweled in bright-colored necklaces and bracelets,
to dance circles surrounding breakers. Smiling faces sweep by,
almost all of them familiar, welcoming me to the community's latest
gathering.
</P>
<P>
   Our community is accepting. At a rave, I can be myself _
whatever incarnation that may be.
</P>
<P>
   Our community also has its problems _ some ravers wake up
``crustified'' from Ecstacy.
</P>
<P>
   But at its essence, the spirit of the rave community is freedom.
When I close my eyes and dance like no one's watching, my soul is
rejuvenated.
</P>
<P>
   T. Chante LaGon, 23, is senior writer for Lunar Magazine and an
active member of the Atlanta Alliance. She has been raving for
about three years.
</P>
<P>
   clagon(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
