   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-EMAIL (Washington) _ The Justice Department has begun a
criminal investigation into whether White House officials illegally
suppressed large numbers of executive office e-mails and concealed
the missing messages by intimidating employees of a non-government
contractor, court documents filed in federal court disclosed
Thursday. By David Johnston and Mark Lacey. (We plan to move the
story by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,500 words.
