<SLUG> BC-BKC-BRASWEL-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BAD NEWS FOR BRASWELL?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Final approval on who will be named men's
basketball coach at Oregon State appears to lie with school
president Paul Risser. And that could be bad news for Bobby
Braswell.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell, Cal State Northridge's coach for the past four
seasons, is a finalist for the Beavers job, but the school did not
announce its choice on Thursday, as was expected.
</P>
<P>
   That probably doesn't bode well for Braswell because it appears
OSU athletic director Mitch Barnhart is going to Risser because his
choice will require a large financial commitment.
</P>
<P>
   That means Colorado State coach Ritchie McKay is probably the
leading candidate. Cash-strapped OSU would have to buy out the
final four years of McKay's contract at $250,000 per season, a
decision that would need Risser's approval.
</P>
<P>
   But Braswell is a firm candidate, especially if negotiations
fail with McKay and, possibly, Milwaukee Bucks assistant Don
Newman.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell, who coached CSUN to a 20-10 season and an appearance
in the Big Sky tournament championship game, is being courted by a
Pac-10 school for the second consecutive year. A year ago, he was a
finalist at Washington State, a position that McKay, 34, reportedly
turned down to stay in Fort Collins.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell fits best in OSU's salary structure. The athletic
department is facing a $5.5 million budget deficit, and on top of
the buyout, McKay reportedly wants more than the $200,000 annual
salary the school paid former Beavers coach Eddie Payne.
</P>
<P>
   Braswell, whose CSUN teams have won five of seven games against
teams coached by McKay and Newman, has a base salary of $92,700 for
a contract that ends in June 2001.
</P>
<P>
   Newman was successful in his one year as as Arizona State's
interim coach _ the Sun Devils were 18-14 and made the National
Invitation Tournament. The Portland Oregonian reported Thursday
that Newman is a friend of OSU football coach Dennis Erickson.
</P>
<P>
   Oregon State needs to make a decision soon because the late
signing period for men's basketball recruits begins April 5.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
