<P>
   No. 8 North Carolina (20-13) vs. No. 4 Tennessee (26-6) NORTH
CAROLINA TAR HEELS
</P>
<P>
   COACH: Bill Guthridge, 3rd season, 78-27. Was a longtime
assistant to the legendary Dean Smith.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STAT: This is not a typically quick Tar Heels team. North
Carolina has only 193 steals, compared with 271 steals recorded by
their opponents.
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: In most of their losses, the Tar Heels had a
large number of turnovers. Point guard Ed Cota is more effective
when he aggressively looks for his shot. Guard Joseph Forte can
create his own shot while center Brendan Haywood can be a force.
Haywood, who had a lackluster NCAA Tournament a year ago, had a
tremendous regional last weekend against Missouri and Stanford.
Opponents have been able to exploit North Carolina's lack of
defensive quickness.
</P>
<P>
   WILL WIN IF: Cota controls the game, Haywood is dominant in the
middle and the Heels limit scoring by Tony Harris and Vincent
Yarbrough.
NORTH CAROLINA STARTERS G ED COTA 6-2 202 Sr. Key stats: 10.3 ppg,
