By WENDELL BARNHOUSE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
No. 1 DUKE (29-4) vs. No. 5 FLORIDA (26-7) When: 6:38 p.m.
DUKE BLUE DEVILS
<TEXT>
<P>
   COACH: Mike Krzyzewski, 25th season, 571-218. The only coach
with a national title to his credit who still has a team in the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STATS: The Blue Devils do an excellent job playing defense
without fouling much. They have made more free throws (601) than
their opponents have attempted (510).
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: The Blue Devils rely on Chris Carrawell's
ability to slash to the basket and Shane Battier's accurate 3-point
shooting. Freshmen Jason Williams (point guard) and Carlos Boozer
(center) have been important contributors. The Blue Devils are able
to get good shots when needed. Defensively, Duke plays a sticky
man-to-man.
</P>
<P>
   WILL WIN IF: It can attack Florida's press to score easy baskets
and its defensive pressure flusters the younger Gators.
DUKE STARTERS G JASON WILLIAMS 6-2 190 Fr. Key stats: 14.5 ppg, 6.5
assists F NATE JAMES 6-6 205 Jr. Key stats: 10.9 ppg, 4.4 rebounds
