   COACH: Tommy Amaker, 3rd season, 52-39. The former Duke star is
making a national name for himself.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STAT: In two NCAA Tournament overtime victories, the Pirates
are 23-of-44 from 3-point range (52.2 percent).
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: The Pirates probably will be without senior
point guard Shaheen Holloway, who injured his ankle in the team's
second-round victory against Temple. Sophomore point guard Ty Shine
scored a career-high 27 points filling in for Holloway and shooting
over Temple's zone. The Pirates rely on the 3-point shot. Amaker
likes to switch defenses to keep the opposition off balance.
</P>
<P>
   WILL WIN IF: The Pirates don't suddenly realize they're just two
victories from a very unlikely Final Four trip.
