   COACH: Eddie Sutton, 30th season, 658-258. He's looking for his
second Final Four trip as the Cowboys' coach.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STAT: In their past 11 games, the Cowboys are shooting 44.7
from 3-point range (88 of 197).
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: The Cowboys are a perfect NCAA Tournament team.
They play tough defense, don't turn the ball over much and they
work until they get good shots. Oklahoma State has six seniors, so
postseason jitters aren't a factor. Oklahoma State can get scoring
from every position but point guard, where Doug Gottlieb struggles
to shoot from the perimeter.
</P>
<P>
   WILL WIN IF: The Cowboys' perimeter defense can prevent Seton
Hall from going crazy from 3-point range.
