<P>
   SRS -- A yearlong Social and Rehabilitation Services study shows
that 35 percent of families who left welfare in Kansas returned to
assistance within six months. Their biggest problems were related
to overdue bills and lack of food. As a result, SRS now has changed
some of its policies so the agency is geared to provide those on
assistance and those who have left with the skills training they
need to obtain and retain jobs. By Donna McGuire.
BUSINESS OFFERINGS
</P>
<P>
   AC -- American Century Investments plans to invest about $100
million in venture capital over the next four years in technology
and Internet-related businesses in Kansas City and around the
country. It would become one of the area's largest venture capital
funds. By Mark Davis
</P>
<P>
   HMO -- Kansas City area HMOs showed mixed financial results for
1999. By Julius A. Karash.
</P>
<P>
   HEASTER -- Business column by Jerry Heaster.
SPORTS OFFERINGS
</P>
<P>
   WHITLOCK -- Sports column by Jason Whitlock, from the NCAA
Midwest Regional in Auburn Hills, Mich.
