Investors, a money management firm in Englewood, Colo., and John D.
Freeman, president of the Investment Research Co., a money manager
in Rancho Santa Fe, proves that two heads are indeed better than
one. Freeman (shown with his wife, Jeanette, and his son, Ben)
picks 170 to 200 stocks using a computer-based mathematical model.
