contours of pop music, with oddball, freaky bits of comedy that
leap out of nowhere. (Shooting Gallery/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) UNDATED -- March 23, 2000 -- CASTLE-DRAWINGS-REVIEW --
To see James Castle's exhibit at the Drawing Center's Drawing Room
is a remarkable experience. His lifelong subject matter was his own
surroundings, sometimes drawn from memory and at other times
directly, but never ``improved'' or prettified. This untitled
drawing by Castle shows his family home in Star, Idaho, and was
created from found paper, soot and spit. (The Drawing Center/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) UNDATED -- March 23, 2000 -- NY-ASIAN-ART -- In these
