<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- March 23, 2000 -- RHEINGOLD-OPERA-REVIEW --
James Morris and Hanna Schwarz in the Metropolitan Opera's
production of ``Das Rheingold.'' The audience sat in rapt attention
for two and a half uninterrupted hours (Wagner fans are the best
behaved) through a dramatically taut and spaciously beautiful
performance. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) NEW YORK -- March 23, 2000 -- THEATER-NOTES -- Daniel
Sullivan is currently the best-represented director in New York,
with three plays running, including ``Dinner With Friends,''
``Ancestral Voices'' and most recently ``A Moon for the
Misbegotten.'' ``I'd love to see something besides my own work,''
Sullivan said recently over a cup of coffee. ``And I'm sure New
York would, too.'' (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) LAGUNA SAN IGNACIO, Mexico -- March 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR
SUN., MAR. 26 -- MEXICO-WHALES-COX-3 -- The San Ignacio Lagoon is
the last gray whale breeding habitat on Baja's coast that is
untouched by commercial development. Every winter, the whales,
which were an endangered species until five years ago, swim into
the lagoon after a 6,000-mile migration from the Arctic Circle.
Whale watchers approach a gray whale in the San Ignacio Lagoon, an
isolated inlet 600 miles south of San Diego and three hours from
the nearest paved road. (Susan Ferriss/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) PUNTA ABREOJOS, Mexico -- March 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR
SUN., MAR. 2 -- MEXICO-WHALES-COX-1 -- The village of Punta
Abreojos with its 1,000 inhabitants has run a fishing cooperative
since the 1930s that exports abalone, lobster and other seafood to
Asia and the United States. As the last gray whale breeding habitat
on Baja's coast that is untouched by commercial development, many
fishermen are developing campsites and whale watching for tourists
here. But that activity only lasts for several months out of the
year. Most have to seek work elsewhere or return to fishing
full-time to make a living. Women from Punta Abreojos shuck abalone
at the prosperous fishing cooperative. (Susan Ferriss/Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) LAGUNA SAN IGNACIO, Mexico -- March 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR
SUN., MAR. 26 -- MEXICO-WHALES-COX-2 -- An isolated inlet 600 miles
south of San Diego and three hours from the nearest paved road, the
San Ignacio Lagoon is the last gray whale breeding habitat on
Baja's coast that is untouched by commercial development. Every
winter, the whales, which were an endangered species until five
years ago, swim into the lagoon after a 6,000-mile migration from
the Arctic Circle. Whale watchers approach a gray whale in the San
Ignacio Lagoon. (Susan Ferriss/Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) WASHINGTON -- March 23, 2000 -- CONGRESS-BUDGET --
Republicans in the House on Thursday worked to push through their
$1.8 trillion budget that calls for some $200 billion in five-year
tax cuts. Rep. John Kasich, left, R-Ohio, discusses the GOP budget
plan during a news conference on Thursday. (Justin Lane/The New
York Times)
