office dress codes and self-expression in the workplace. Kirsten
Blocker, left, is an editor at the Boston-based female youth
magazine Teen Voices and a 21-year-old English major at Pine Manor
College in Chestnut Hill. Shari Thurer, 52, is a psychologist in
private practice and an adjunct professor at Boston University. As
they began debating over dinner recently, the two were quick to
engage in some bashing of the recently released movie ``Erin
Brockovich'' starring Julia Roberts. (Wendy Maeda/The Boston Globe)
