   (NYT49) NEW YORK -- March 23, 2000 -- STUDENTS-DRUGS -- Whether
it's stimulants, pain killers, anti-depressants or anti-psychotic
drugs, mixing and matching the legal drugs overflowing American's
medicine cabinets is becoming today's favored drug experience for
many students. Katherine Plyshevsky, 21, a junior at New York
University, used Ritalin to help her through her midterm exams.
``It was actually fun to do the work,'' she said. (Marilynn K.
Yee/The New York Times)
