<P>
   (NYT20) LAGUNA SAN IGNACIO, Mexico -- March 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR
SUN., MAR. 26 -- MEXICO-WHALES-COX-3 -- The San Ignacio Lagoon is
the last gray whale breeding habitat on Baja's coast that is
untouched by commercial development. Every winter, the whales,
which were an endangered species until five years ago, swim into
the lagoon after a 6,000-mile migration from the Arctic Circle.
Whale watchers approach a gray whale in the San Ignacio Lagoon, an
isolated inlet 600 miles south of San Diego and three hours from
the nearest paved road. (Susan Ferriss/Cox News Service)
